[1] Russia (Astrakhan)
Date: Fri 4 Oct 2013
Source: MK.RU TV [In Russian, trans. & edited - Mod.CP]
http://www.mk.ru/social/health/news/2013/10/04/925957-uzhe-vo-vtorom-vuze-astrahani-zafiksirovana-vspyishka-kori.html

A 2nd outbreak of measles recorded in an educational institution in the Astrakhan Oblast
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Some students at Astrakhan State University (ASU) have been admitted to the Regional Infectious Diseases Hospital with a diagnosis of measles virus infection, according to Svetlana Smrnova, the Deputy Minister of Health. This is the 2nd occasion in recent years that cases of measles virus infection in an educational institution have resulted in hospitalisation.

At the beginning of September [2013] a student from Dagestan was diagnosed with measles virus infection and was quarantined in the Astrakhan Medical Academy (ASMA). Subsequently 27 students were diagnosed with measles virus infection by laboratory investigation. As a consequence, on the basis of these cases, more than 5200 people, including more than 3000 students, were vaccinated against measles.

An extensive survey was undertaken to differentiate measles cases from other infectious diseases on the basis of clinical features. Measures were undertaken to restrict the outbreak to the one institution and to undertake supplementary vaccination to prevent further spread of the outbreak.

"We have determined now that the focus of the outbreak is confined to the sick students in the ASU. Mass immunisation and 'daily checkups' have been initiated to prevent spread of the outbreak to any other institution."

--
