[4] Australia (Queensland)
Date: Tue 1 Oct 2013
Source: Nine MSN [edited]
http://news.ninemsn.com.au/health/2013/10/01/14/26/eighteenth-measles-case-confirmed-in-qld


18th measles case confirmed in Queensland
-----------------------------------------
In the latest case, the infected person visited Ipswich police station and the Ipswich Courthouse a number of times between 23 and 27 Sep 2013 as well as UFS pharmacy at Booval on 26 Sep 2013.

Public health physician Dr Heidi Carroll says those who have visited these areas should be alert for measles symptoms, particularly if they have not been vaccinated against the potentially deadly disease.

The new case was the 8th in the Ipswich area this year [2013], Dr Carroll said.

--
